How many people are affected by cri-du-chat syndrome ?,"Cri-du-chat syndrome occurs in an estimated 1 in 20,000 to 50,000 newborns. This condition is found in people of all ethnic backgrounds.",GHR,cri-du-chat syndrome
What are the genetic changes related to cri-du-chat syndrome ?,"Cri-du-chat syndrome is caused by a deletion of the end of the short (p) arm of chromosome 5. This chromosomal change is written as 5p-. The size of the deletion varies among affected individuals;
